<item>
            <title>[LU-13269] make lnet-selftest.sh more flexible</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13269</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lnet-selftest.sh adds both LST tests: from client to server and from server to client, but sometimes we are interesting to execute the tests only from server or only from client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch allows to set required &quot;from&quot; parameter via lst_FROM variable.&lt;br/&gt;
The following values are used:&lt;br/&gt;
lst_FROM=c : add the tests from clients to server only&lt;br/&gt;
lst_FROM=s : add the tests from server to clients only&lt;/p&gt;</description>
